    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "To update:\r\n\r\n* The bug seems to be gone with the current tip of master - running the repro client for a long time doesn't hit the issue, but I'm not sure where it's fixed (rebased the repro in https://github.com/apolcyn/grpc/tree/repro_send_close_race_latest_master)\r\n\r\n* The problem still seems to happen in the current v1.0.x tip - it still repros very quickly with https://github.com/apolcyn/grpc/tree/repro_send_close_race_latest_v10x\r\n\r\nWhere the problem does occur: \r\n* After a minor change to the repro client, running under tsan shows nothing suspicious (update in https://github.com/apolcyn/grpc/tree/repro_send_close_race)\r\n* The problem seems to go away if locks are tweaked so that a thread switch can never happen between calls to start_batch and pluck."
